A study conducted by Harvard University found that nations with poor performing economies are more likely to suffer from heart-related illnesses, which puts SA firmly in the red zone. In the last 30 years, cardiovascular disease rates are estimated to have increased by over a 100% in developing countries where economic growth has typically been poor. Samora Mangesi spoke to Nicole Jennings, spokesperson for Pharma Dynamics, the largest provider of heart medication in the country... --ChannelAfrica--